summary: This is a joint letter from the prosecution and defense in the case of United States v. Maxwell, proposing an extension of the deadline to file a letter regarding the pretrial schedule. It is a procedural communication from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York.

persons.name: Assistant United States Attorney
persons.context: The sender of the email and attached joint letter, representing the United States in the case against Maxwell.

keyFacts: The document is a joint letter from the parties in US v. Maxwell.
The letter proposes an extension of the deadline to file a pretrial schedule letter.
The case involves Ghislaine Maxwell, though she is not explicitly named in the provided text fragment.
